<P>
   TREATY-REACT (United Nations) _ Around the world, government
leaders and arms experts react with dismay and even anger after the
U.S. Senate defeated, without much debate, a nuclear test ban
treaty that had been decades in the making. For many, there was a
sense that the treaty may now be dead. By Barbara Crossette.
