   TREATY-ASSESS (Washington) _ Analysis: Partisanship overwhelms
the Senate. By Adam Clymer.
</P>
<P>
   NAZI-GOLD-TRAIN (Washington) _ In the last weeks of World War
II, as Soviet troops advanced from the east, Nazi officials in
Hungary ordered that a train be sent west toward Germany with the
collected wealth of Hungary's decimated Jews. Their wedding bands
alone filled crate after crate. U.S. troops intercepted the train
in Austria, in May 1945, and moved its contents _ gold, silver,
paintings, furs _ to a warehouse near Salzburg. But according to a
preliminary report by U.S. investigators, the Americans were
neither careful nor selfless custodians. By Tim Golden.
</P>
