<P>
   ART-CENTURY _ NEW YORK _ A review of The American Century, Part
2 at the Whitney Museum of Art. The art and history show looks at
the seocnd half of the 20th century. (Fox, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 20. EMBARGOED FOR SUNDAY
</P>
<P>
   MOVIES-OMEGA _ When the Christian film industry makes an
evangelical film, it usually does pretty well _ with evangelical
Christians. But the
hit-them-over-the-head-with-Jesus-until-they-see-the-light-genre
hasn't worked as well with the vast swath of Americans who go to
the movies purely to be entertained. So when Stephan Blinn set out
to write the screenplay for the evangelical Christian thriller The
Omega Code, which opens today, he knew he had to walk a fine line
between secular storytelling and proselytizing. His hope is that
the action-adventure will hold together on its secular merits _ and
if it provokes some conversation about what's in the Bible, so much
the better. (Palm Beach Post). 20.
</P>
<P>
   REVIEW-OMEGA _ Movie review: ``The Omega Code,'' new prophecy
movie from Trinity Broadcasting Network and starring Michael York
and Casper Van Dien. (Longino, Cox News Service). 10.
</P>
<P>
   TV-CAULFIELD _ Combine the frat boy craziness of Beverly Hills,
90210 with the gritty realism of NYPD Blue and what do you get?
Ryan Caulfield: Year One, a surprisingly tender, though totally
predictable cop drama. Ryan Caulfield (Sean Maher) is a 19-year-old
rookie cop patrolling Philadelphia's toughest streets. (Palm Beach
Post). 16.
</P>
