<P>
   CoxNet SCIHEALTH 1012 -- When a child is diagnosed with juvenile
diabetes, controlling diet and blood sugars becomes a constant
concern. It truly is a balancing act of life and death. (Lamb,
Dayton Daily News) Art includes a 3-column color photo of a boy
giving himself a blood test.
</P>
<P>
   WITH: TREATING SCHIZOPHRENIA -- The benefits of psychotherapy
and social support, long recognized in treating depressive
disorders, also are gaining acceptance as an essential element in
treating schizophrenia and other mental illnesses that involve
psychoses. (Lamb, Dayton Daily News)
</P>
<P>
   WITH: DEPRESSION -- Things you should know about depression.
(Lamb, Dayton Daily News) With info box: warning signs of
depression.
</P>
<P>
   WITH: MEDICAL PAPERWORK -- Don't get mad over the piles of
forms, get organized! (Lore, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   HEALTH &AMP; MEDIA -- Health books and Internet sites on health
issues. (Staff, Cox News Service) Art includes three 6-pica color
photos of book jackets and 1 6-pica color illustration of a
computer.
</P>
<P>
   DYSTROPHY-SURVIVORS _ WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ Who will care for
the Eldred Boys? Insurers thought muscular dystrophy would kill
Dwight and Christopher Eldred by their 16th birthdays. It didn't.
And now their parents have nowhere to turn for money to keep them
alive. (Palm Beach Post) WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
<P>
   FLU _ DAYTON, Ohio _ Early indications suggest the flu season
will arrive sooner and hit harder this winter than in normal years.
On the bright side, though, doctors will be able to battle
influenza with a newly approved prescription drug. ``It's always
speculation as to whether the numbers are going to be high,'' says
Greg Rozelle, director of the personal health division for the
Combined Health District of Montgomery County, Ohio. ``But there's
a little bit of a difference in the vaccine this year. When the
strains change, more people tend to get sick.'' Public health
officials are predicting flu to strike four weeks earlier than
usual because of a strain that infected people on Alaskan cruise
ships the past two summers. (Lamb, Dayton Daily News) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   EXERCISE _ As evening falls earlier, five things you should know
about exercising in twilight. (Kim, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
