<P>
   AMBUSH-TEXAS (Pleasanton, Texas) _ A longtime friend and
roommate of Jeremiah Engleton is arrested and charged with capital
murder several hours after he told a neighbor that he knew Engleton
was planning to kill law enforcement officers. Kenneth Vodochodsky,
19, is charged with three counts of capital murder and two counts
of attempted capital murder in connection with the attack Tuesday
night that killed two deputies and a state trooper. By JAMES
PINKERTON.
</P>
