<P>
   THOMPSON-COLUMN (Washington) _ In his zeal to escape the stigma
of right-wing negativism, George W. Bush seems to have learned a
lesson from the defeat of Republican presidential nominee Thomas E.
Dewey in 1948. The lesson is to avoid being weighted down with the
lackluster performance of a hardline conservative Congress. By
ROBERT E. THOMPSON. (Filed Wednesday.)
