By Tim Weiner.
</P>
<P>
   PAKISTAN-MOOD (Islamabad, Pakistan) _ Right now, Pakistanis,
happy to be rid of Prime Minister Nawaz Sharif, are pleased with
the coup. But they may not be nearly as happy about military rule.
By Tim Weiner and Steve Levine.
</P>
<P>
   NOBEL-PEACE-PRIZE (Paris) _ The Nobel Peace Price goes to
Doctors Without Borders, set up in 1971 by 10 French doctors. They
claim a right to intervene in any country to treat the wounded,
sick and starving, from Biafra to Timor, and have worked in 80
countries. By Suzanne Daley.
</P>
<P>
   CLINTON-TREATY (Washington) _ Is the defeat of the test ban
treaty simply a sign of problems between Clinton and the Senate _
or is it a sign of a bigger breakoff between the presidency and the
Senate that could have ramifications for years to come? By Adam
Clymer.
</P>
<P>
