For Release SATURDAY AMs, October 16, 1999  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Boston Globe plans to move the following stories for use by
NYTimes News Service clients.
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR; For questions about stories, contact  &UR; Roy Greene  &LR; at the
Boston Globe,  &UR; 617-929-2597. &LR;  For individual purchase of graphics
or photos please call 212 556-4204 or -1927.
</P>
<P>
   All stories will bear the BOS designator.
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; INTERNATIONAL (i) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   RUSSIA-CHECHNYA (Moscow) _ Russians take a strategic town as
they mount offensive that appears aimed at the Chechen capital of
Grozny. By David Filipov. 750 words.
</P>
<P>
