   DOW _ Once again, Alan Greenspan has roiled the stock market.
His comments late Thursday, combined with inflationary looking news
in the latest economic report, hammers stocks in the early going.
The Dow loses more than 200 points before rebounding slightly.
(Walker, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   LOEWS _ ATLANTA _ Lowe's announced a major expansion of its
Internet retailing efforts. The home improvement retailer has spun
off its Internet staff into a separate group of 50 people as Lowe's
tries to beat Home Depot to Web sales. Trying to find out how this
will impact Lowe's online sales debut. (Bond, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
