<P>
   FBC-HAMILTON _ ATLANTA _ Georgia Tech quarterback Joe Hamilton
has emerged as a media darling in the race for the Heisman Trophy.
ESPN commentators have been effusive in their praise, and ABC's
Terry Bowden says Hamilton as his top pick. But what do the Heisman
voters have to say? And how much did his subpar performance against
North Carolina last week affect his standing? (Clemons, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 15.
</P>
<P>
   FBC-WARRICK _ ATLANTA _ A look at Peter Warrick's Heisman Trophy
chances in light of his arrest on a felony theft charge. Some
voters say he's done. Others say he still has a shot. Warrick went
on national TV to apologize last week and may be back for Florida
State's game at Clemson on Oct. 23. And if Warrick doesn't make it
back, who are some of the challengers to Joe Hamilton? (Barnhart,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
