<P>
   COXNET NASCAR 101-- Most thought Dale Earnhardt was past his
prime a couple of years ago. He wasn't winning, and there were some
bizarre incidents -- like going to sleep in his car moments before
the race, then wrecking on the first lap without contact. But just
when it appeared safe to write him off, he returns with a
vengeance, moving to No. 7 on the points list. (Carvell, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
