<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Feeling creative? Try on these costume ideas
 &HT;    By Staff Reports
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   WACO, Texas _ Scrounge around your house or head to the discount
and thrift stores to find the items needed for these fun Halloween
costumes:
</P>
<P>
   AUSTIN POWERS:
</P>
<P>
   _ Bell bottom velvet leisure suit
</P>
<P>
   _ Ruffled shirt
</P>
<P>
   _ Cheap jewelry
</P>
<P>
   _ Big black glasses
</P>
<P>
   _ Brown wig
</P>
<P>
   DR. EVIL:
</P>
<P>
   _ Fake bald head
</P>
<P>
   _ Gray suit, white shirt, white tennis shoes
</P>
<P>
   _ Carry around a stuffed cat (or a toddler dressed the same way
for Mini Me).
</P>
<P>
   FELICITY SHAGWELL:
</P>
<P>
   _ Blue velvet short sleeve tank top
</P>
<P>
   _ Really short matching blue velvet shorts
</P>
<P>
   _ Long blonde wig
</P>
<P>
   MUMMY FROM THE MOVIE ``THE MUMMY:''
</P>
<P>
   _ White sheets or gauze, torn into long strips
</P>
<P>
   _ Wrap them around the body and around the head. Walk with a
limp.
</P>
<P>
   DILBERT:
</P>
<P>
   _ Round wire frame glasses
</P>
<P>
   _ White shirt and black dress slacks
</P>
<P>
   _ Red and white striped tie, pipe cleaners
</P>
<P>
   _ Glue pipe cleaners to the underside of the tie so that it will
form the upward bend that Dilbert wears.
</P>
<P>
   JUDGE JUDY:
</P>
<P>
   _ Graduation robe
</P>
<P>
   _ Gray wig
</P>
<P>
   _ Lace-trimmed blouse
</P>
<P>
   POST-IT NOTE:
</P>
<P>
   _ Two 3-foot pieces of cardboard
</P>
<P>
   _ Large yellow sheet of posterboard
</P>
<P>
   _ Sponge
</P>
<P>
   _ Light gray paint
</P>
<P>
   _ Magic Marker
</P>
<P>
   _ String
</P>
<P>
   _ Glue posterboard to one side of cardboard. Apply light coating
of gray paint across the top 1/8 of one board with sponge. Write
short note on front side of one board with Magic Marker. Use string
to attach two sides together.
</P>
<P>
   ``A COSTUME:''
</P>
<P>
   _ Plain T-shirt, any color
</P>
<P>
   _ Fabric paints
</P>
<P>
   _ Write ``COSTUME'' on the shirt using paints, and you're
anything you want to be.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
