<TEXT>
<P>
   Editors note:
</P>
<P>
   The photo numbered NYT16 sent Thursday, Oct. 14, by the New York
Times News Service, with an article about reports of war time
American military looting of valuables stolen from Hungarian Jews,
was provided in error. The photo was slugged: JEWS-GOLD-1-B&AMP;W.
</P>
<P>
   The photo should have shown Gen. Harry J. Collins a commander
suspected of having requisitioned valuables for his personal use.
</P>
<P>
   Instead it showed Gen. J. Lawton Collins, who died in 1987. He
was a combat leader in World War II and an Army chief of staff. He
won the nickname ``Lightning Joe'' when he commanded a division at
Guadalcanal. He later led one of the Army corps that landed at
Normandy on D-Day. The general earned numerous honors including two
Silver Stars.
</P>
<P>
   We have moved NYT555, slugged: SUB-JEWS-GOLD-1-B&AMP;W, of Gen.
Harry J. Collins, to replace the photo moved yesterday in error.
</P>
<P>
   If you have any questions, please call 212-556-4204 or
888-603-1036.
</P>
