<P>
   SUSANA-CANCER (Los Angeles) _ The state health department lied
to the public about health risks linked to the Santa Susana Field
Lab, according to a damning report released Friday. After a study
of cancer cases among workers at the lab, officials of the state
Department of Health Services assured the public there would be a
broader community health study, but in private the same officials
decided such a study was pointless and dropped it. By Terri Hardy.
(Will move in the ``n'' California news file.)
