<P>
   PRESIDENT'S AGENDA THREATENED BY TENUOUS RELATIONS WITH CONGRESS
</P>
<P>
   With Sidebar: Clinton-Data
</P>
<P>
   Moving on Washington (w) and Political (P) categories
</P>
<P>
   By Bob Deans
</P>
<P>
   Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   WASHINGTON _ After accusing his Republican foes on Capitol Hill
of turning their backs on the rest of the world, undermining the
national economy and attacking the nation's teachers, police,
environment and the poor, President Clinton suddenly shifted gears.
</P>
<P>
   ``I want to work with Congress,'' Clinton said Thursday,
